#week-title("Three", "Planetary Hours & Aspects")

=== Core Teaching

This week focuses on the practical calculation of *Planetary Hours* and the
meaning of *Aspects* in the laboratory.

Planetary hours rotate through the day in a fixed sequence. Aspects (the angles
between planets) correspond to laboratory operations:
- *Conjunction:* Cohobation or reunion.
- *Opposition:* Separation or distillation.
- *Trine:* Harmony of elements.

Understanding these links allows the alchemist to "read" the sky as a sequence of
laboratory instructions.

=== Topics This Week

- Calculating Planetary Hours in depth
- Aspects and their laboratory equivalents
- Spherical attributions on the Tree of Life
- Using NDT numbers to understand astrological cycles

#inner-work[
  *The Hour of the Planet*

  Practice calculating the planetary hours for your location for three consecutive
  days. Match your laboratory cleaning or maintenance to the hour of Mercury or
  Saturn.

  Does the work feel more "orderly" or "fluid" depending on the hour? Record your
  findings in your laboratory log.
]

